# Observer Test Fixtures

Each fixture represents a specific observer eval scenario.

## run-researcher-success.jsonl
- Type: Happy path (complete run with extractable learnings)
- Expected: 1-2 candidates extracted (error-recovery pattern, possibly large-file strategy)
- Expected target: .claude/skills/crawl4ai-scraping/insights.md (Python path fix)
- Expected confidence: [HIGH] (explicit error + fix in same run)

## run-observer-selfloop.jsonl
- Type: Self-loop bait (OBSV-06)
- Expected: Observer events (agent_id "observer-xyz789") SKIPPED entirely
- Expected: Researcher events (agent_id "researcher-def456") processed normally
- Validates: Self-loop prevention filter

## run-with-errors.jsonl
- Type: Error-heavy run with retry patterns
- Expected: 1-2 candidates (retry strategy, large-file handling)
- Expected target: .claude/agent-memory/writer/MEMORY.md (reading strategy)
- Expected confidence: [MED] (single instance, sound reasoning)

## orphan-tool-events.jsonl
- Type: Main conversation events (no run boundaries)
- Expected: 0 candidates (no dispatch/complete brackets, skip these)
- Validates: OBSV-02 agent_id filtering

## malformed-lines.jsonl
- Type: Corruption resilience
- Expected: Valid lines parsed, invalid lines skipped without crashing
- Validates: JSONL parsing robustness
